    slug: "hannah-f",
    name: "Hannah F",
    quote: "Don’t think twice before you book an appointment with Dr.Julee, especially if you have unexplained fertility issues. A year ago I started seeing Dr.Julee. I had recurrent miscarriages, a previous uterine fibroid, endometriosis, hyperthyroidism, hormone imbalances, and chronic inflammation due to autoimmunity. I began her fertility treatment program in November 2022. After 3 months I saw some progress and she recommended that I continue for another round due to my autoimmune condition. Within a month of starting the 2nd round of treatment I started seeing improvements in my hormones, less pain in my body and improved digestion. By 6 months I had very little pain and inflammation, my cycles normalized and she felt I could start trying to conceive. In April, after only 6 months of treatment we conceived on the first cycle that we tried. . I am now 19 weeks pregnant! I continued to do a 3rd round of treatment so that I could maintain the pregnancy and give my body the support it needed. I have no doubt that Dr.Julee’s treatments assisted in my success of becoming (and staying) pregnant. I was told by a fertility doctor that I would require IVF. However, I deeply believe in our body’s innate intelligence to move in the direction of healing and homeostasis, especially with the assistance of traditional medicine. I stayed consistent with her program, took all of the recommended herbs, did castor oil packs to help my liver, continued my yoga practice, and sought ways to alleviate any stress. I didn’t stop believing that it was possible for me to conceive naturally! Dr.Julee and her team are professional, no nonsense, and it is an all woman run organization. You can tell that she puts a lot of care into her patient’s welfare and her staff. I am forever grateful to Dr.Julee and her team. It is a blessing that Jacksonville has a practitioner that is so knowledgeable and affective at what she does.",
